Description: Fragment of floor of Attic black-glazed pottery cup-skyphos. Fine-walled. Interior glazed with central motif of ill-fitting impressed tongues. Moulded rings on underside, reserved; glazed to either side. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 600)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1537)
